The paper focuses on mobile network quality and user satisfaction, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). Additionally, the study involves collecting data from users through questionnaires, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of mobile devices and the analysis of network measurements also align with the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for modeling user satisfaction, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
